<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
	<meta charset="utf-8" />
	<title>Application</title>
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/dude.css">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto:ital,wght@0,100..900;1,100..900&display=swap">
</head>
<body>
    <h1>üé≠ The Joke Factory üé≠</h1>
    <p>Submit your best (or worst) jokes below! Our team of highly unqualified judges will... probably ignore them.</p>
    
    <form action="/apply" method="post">
        <fieldset>
            <legend>Your Information</legend>
            <label>
                Name: 
                <input required type="text" name="name" placeholder="Your name or stage name"/>
            </label>
        </fieldset>
        
        <fieldset>
            <legend>Joke Details</legend>
            
            <label>
                Type: 
                <input required type="text" name="type" id="joke-type" placeholder="e.g., Knock-knock, Dad joke, Pun"/>
                <span class="tooltip" title="Common joke types: Knock-knock, Dad joke, Pun, One-liner, Observational, Dark humor">‚ÑπÔ∏è</span>
            </label>
            
            <div id="joke-type-suggestions">
                <div class="type-bubble" onclick="document.getElementById('joke-type').value = 'Dad joke'">Dad joke</div>
                <div class="type-bubble" onclick="document.getElementById('joke-type').value = 'Knock-knock'">Knock-knock</div>
                <div class="type-bubble" onclick="document.getElementById('joke-type').value = 'Pun'">Pun</div>
                <div class="type-bubble" onclick="document.getElementById('joke-type').value = 'One-liner'">One-liner</div>
                <div class="type-bubble" onclick="document.getElementById('joke-type').value = 'Observational'">Observational</div>
            </div>
            
            <label>
                Setup: 
                <input required type="text" name="setup" id="setup" placeholder="The beginning of your joke" maxlength="100"/>
                <div id="character-counter"><span id="setup-count">0</span>/100</div>
            </label>
            
            <div class="joke-example">
                <p><span class="good">Good setup example:</span> "Why don't scientists trust atoms?"</p>
                <p><span class="bad">Bad setup example:</span> "So there's this thing about science..."</p>
                <p>Tip: Your setup should create expectation but not give away the punchline!</p>
            </div>
            
            <label>
                Punchline: 
                <input required type="text" name="punchline" id="punchline" placeholder="The funny payoff" maxlength="100"/>
                <div id="character-counter"><span id="punchline-count">0</span>/100</div>
            </label>
            
            <div class="joke-example">
                <p><span class="good">Good punchline example:</span> "Because they make up everything!" 
                    <span class="emoji-rating">üòÇ</span></p>
                <p><span class="bad">Bad punchline example:</span> "Because atoms are small." 
                    <span class="emoji-rating">üòê</span></p>
                <p>Tip: The punchline should subvert expectations in a clever way!</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="joke-example">
                <h3>Complete Joke Examples:</h3>
                <p><strong>Good:</strong> "I'm reading a book about anti-gravity. It's impossible to put down!" 
                    <span class="emoji-rating">ü§£</span></p>
                <p><strong>Bad:</strong> "Books are heavy. Gravity makes them fall." 
                    <span class="emoji-rating">üí§</span></p>
            </div>
        </fieldset>

        <div style="text-align: center;">
            <input type="reset" value="Start Over" />
            <input type="submit" value="Submit My Masterpiece!"/>
        </div>
        
        <hr>
        <div style="text-align: center;">
            <a href="/"> HOME</a> | 
            <a href="#" onclick="alert('Joke writing tip: The key to humor is surprise! Make your punchline unexpected but still make sense.')"> Joke Tip</a> |
        </div>
    </form>